This paper deals with image recognition using deep neural networks and machine learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of SIFT features also suggests that the paper may fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which is a common topic in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of data-driven frameworks and automated feature extraction suggests that the paper may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
